<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 86-year-old man was hospitalized Monday night after he was stabbed in the 
abdomen while in his back yard in the 3000 block of National Avenue, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Aurelio Casillas, 86, thought he heard a prowler about 10:30 p.m. and went out 
investigate. When Casillas confronted a man, he stabbed Casillas several times 
and fled, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Casillas was flown by Life Flight to UC San Diego Medical Center, where he 
underwent surgery Monday. He was in serious condition Tuesday, a hospital 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
