<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTHER TERESA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a world where heroes and heroines are few, the article "Mother Teresa Brings 
a Message of Hope to Homeless Latino Youths in Los Angeles" (Metro, Feb. 1) 
gave your readers a chance to hope again. Mother Teresa's visit to those 
homeless youngsters definitely showed a "message of love." 
</P>
<P>
As a teen-ager I know that it is important for adolescents to have role models. 
Mother Teresa gives everyone a special message. Love is vital to human life. 
This woman has shown us how to reach out to others with care and concern. 
</P>
<P>
She challenges us to do the same -- to give without expecting something in 
return. Is this not a possible solution for those who fill their lives with 
drugs, harmful relationships, and overemphasis upon material possessions? We 
must give of our love to those in need. 
</P>
<P>
REBECCA GIRARD 
</P>
<P>
Venice 
