<HEADLINE>
<P>
WILL ON 'RACIAL SPOILS SYSTEM' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The truth about "affirmative action" is that we've always had it. It's not a 
new-fangled liberal idea to help minorities, as many claim. 
</P>
<P>
The "old boy network" -- nepotism, cronyism, member-of-the-club and alumni-ism 
to help favored sons -- was the most successful affirmative action program ever 
devised. The only difference is the recipients of this affirmative action were 
wealthy white males . . . and still are! Do you think J. Danforth Quayle got 
ahead on "merit"? 
</P>
<P>
The question is not whether we will love "affirmative action," but who it will 
benefit. Why not give minorities and women a chance? 
</P>
<P>
JOANNE MURPHY 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
