<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UNSEEDED CAMPORESE UPSETS MECIR IN OPENING ROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Unheralded Italian Omar Camporese upset second-seeded Miloslav Mecir of 
Czechoslovakia, 6-4, 7-6, Tuesday in the opening round of the $492,500 Stella 
Artois indoor tournament at Milan, Italy. 
</P>
<P>
Mecir, 24, who reached the final of the Australian Open at Melbourne last 
month, couldn't handle the powerful serve of Camporese, a wild-card entry who 
is ranked 204th in the world. 
</P>
<P>
In another surprise, Soviet qualifier Andrei Cherkasov eliminated 
seventh-seeded Henri Leconte of France, 7-6, 4-6, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
Fourth-seeded Jakob Hlasek of Switzerland beat Marco Ostoja of Yugoslavia, 7-6, 
6-1. 
</P>
<P>
Monica Seles of Yugoslavia surprised seventh-seeded Larisa Savchenko of the 
Soviet Union, 6-0, 6-2, to advance to the second round of the $300,000 Virginia 
Slims of Washington at Fairfax, Va. 
</P>
<P>
Steffi Graf surrendered only five points on her serve in a 6-1, 6-1 victory 
over Stacey Martin, a University of Tennessee freshman. Graf, the world's 
top-ranked player, needed only 39 minutes to win. 
</P>
<P>
Third-seeded Manuela Maleeva of Bulgaria topped Czechoslovakia's Andrea 
Holikova, 6-2, 6-4, and Carling Bassett-Seguso of Canada returned from a 
three-month hiatus to defeat Renata Baranski, 6-3, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
Fourth-seeded Natalia Zvereva of the Soviet Union ousted Camile Benjamin, 7-5, 
6-1. 
</P>
<P>
Ninth-seeded Amos Mansdorf of Israel came from behind to defeat Glenn Michibata 
of Canada, 5-7, 6-1, 6-1, in a second-round match at the Volvo Indoor Tennis 
Championships at Memphis, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Andre Agassi routed unseeded Jim Pugh, 6-2, 6-3. Sixth-seeded Brad 
Gilbert defeated Scott Davis, 6-2, 6-1, 11th-seeded Michael Chang beat Tom 
Nijssen of the Netherlands, 6-1, 6-3, and seventh-seeded Kevin Curren beat 
Richard Matuszewski, 6-3, 4-6, 6-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
