<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: PYRAMID LAKE REOPENS WITH IMPROVED BASS BITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pyramid Lake, closed for nearly a week because of snow and ice, reopened Sunday 
with a vastly improved striped bass bite. 
</P>
<P>
Simi Valley resident Paul Selkirk caught six stripers totaling 49 pounds. 
Meanwhile, Westchester's Bob Hanley, who caught two stripers weighing 18 pounds 
Sunday, caught two more on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
LAKE MEAD -- Striped and largemouth bass biting mostly in Vegas and Government 
wash areas. Live shad and frozen anchovies working best for stripers; plastic 
worms best bet for largemouth. 
</P>
<P>
BULLHEAD CITY -- Trout to 2 pounds biting in river, with most baits working. 
Lake fishermen catching fewer fish, but some to 4 pounds. Catfish biting best 
in Topock Marsh. 
</P>
<P>
SALTON SEA -- Orangemouth corvina bite fair at Red Hill and Mulet Island. 
Artificial lures working best. Croaker picking up, biting best at Bombay Beach. 
</P>
<P>
LAKE CACHUMA -- Trout biting near dam and island. Largemouth bass slow, biting 
spotty, biting best in main channel off rocky shoreline. Smallmouth bass taking 
small crawfish off rocky shorelines. 
</P>
<P>
LAKE CASITAS -- Largemouth bass picking up, biting primarily on plastic worms 
and crawfish at 20-25 feet. Mark Simpson, Oxnard, 11-pound bass. Trollers using 
lead-core line at 20 feet catching most trout. 
</P>
<P>
PYRAMID LAKE -- Striped bass picking up, biting best in marina. 
</P>
<P>
LAKE PIRU -- Trout fishing fair, biting best near marina. Cheese-based baits 
working best. Largemouth bass picking up, biting throughout lake. Plastic worms 
best bet. Catfish slow. 
</P>
<P>
LAKE CASTAIC -- Largemouth bass biting best in upper lake. Ed Lishok, Norwalk, 
three bass totaling 22 pounds. Trout biting in both lakes on most baits. 
</P>
<P>
IRVINE LAKE -- Trout bite best at Trout Island, Sierra Cove and Red Cliffs. Tim 
Cerny, Anaheim, 10-6 trout, caught on nightcrawler. 
</P>
<P>
LAKE SKINNER -- Several limits of trout, most between 1-2 pounds. Marina and 
bays across from marina best areas. Largemouth bass slow, with fish averaging 2 
1/2 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
LAKE SILVERWOOD -- Striped bass picking up, biting best near dam. Richard 
Gerhard, San Bernardino, 18-pound striper, caught near dam. Crappie and 
largemouth bass biting under docks. 
</P>
<P>
LAKE HENSHAW -- Crappie bite good under docks. 
</P>
<P>
Trout Plants 
</P>
<P>
LOS ANGELES -- Big Rock Creek, Lake Castaic, Castaic Lagoon, Crystal Lake, Legg 
Lakes, Little Rock Reservoir, Lake Pyramid. 
</P>
<P>
ORANGE -- Laguna Niguel Park Lake. 
</P>
<P>
RIVERSIDE -- Cahuilla Lake, Perris Lake, Lake Skinner. 
</P>
<P>
SAN BERNARDINO -- Glen Helen Park Lake, Mojave Narrows Park Lake. 
</P>
<P>
SAN DIEGO -- Cuyamaca Lake. 
</P>
<P>
VENTURA -- Matilijia Creek, Santa Paula Creek, Lake Piru. 
</P>
<P>
IMPERIAL -- Sunbeam Lake, Weist Lake. 
</P>
<P>
KERN -- Hart Park Lake, Kern River (Borell Powerhouse to Democrat Dam, KR3 
Powerhouse to Lake Isabella), Lake Ming. 
</P>
</TEXT>
