<TEXT>
<P>
Molecular Biosystems reported a third-quarter profit of $1.2 million on revenue 
of $3 million, compared with a profit of $961,578 on revenue of $2.1 million 
over the same period last year. 
</P>
<P>
For the nine months ended Dec. 31, the company's profit was $1.6 million on 
revenue of $6.1 million, up from a profit of $1.4 million on revenue of $4.3 
million over the same three quarters the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
Molecular Biosystems generates minimal revenue from product sales. However, the 
company has signed multimillion-dollar marketing and research agreements with 
Nycomed of Norway and Mallinckrodt of St. Louis covering Albunex, an ultrasound 
imaging product under development. 
</P>
<P>
The company's profit and revenue flow mainly from licensing and research funds 
paid by the two companies. 
