<TEXT>
<P>
ITT Corp.'s 1988 profit fell 15% to $817 million from a restated $965 million 
last year. Sales totaled $19.4 billion, up 6%. For the fourth quarter, earnings 
totaled $180 million, down from a restated profit of $421 million, on revenue 
of $5.2 billion, up 8%. The New York diversified firm said the annual results 
were reduced by a $41-million after-tax provision primarily for several 
environmental cleanup operations at its Southern Wood Piedmont unit as well as 
reduced tax benefits. The firm noted that operating income at its nine business 
segments and Alcatel N.V., a telecommunications joint venture with a European 
firm, rose 36%. 
