<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN and Shauna Snow, Arts and entertainment reports from The 
Times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KCBS-TV Channel 2 will launch a half-hour, 6 a.m. weekday newscast, beginning 
Feb. 27, General Manager Robert Hyland announced Tuesday. "Action News Early 
Report" will be anchored by Jim Moret (who handles the local news cut-ins to 
"CBS This Morning"), with veteran broadcaster Bill Keene providing traffic and 
weather updates. Also featured will be a daily wrap-up from Sports Director 
Keith Olbermann and other news segments. The announcement comes two weeks after 
rival KABC-TV Channel 7 announced plans to launch a half-hour early morning 
newscast (to be aired at either 6 or 6:30 a.m.) in coming months. KNBC-TV 
Channel 4 has a locally-produced newscast that airs at 6:30 a.m. ALEENE MacMINN 
and Shauna Snow 
</P>
</TEXT>
