<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPOTLIGHT: SAN DIEGO ENTERTAINMENT BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego Opera general director Ian Campbell announced several artists for his 
company's production of "Boris Godunov," the opening event of San Diego's 
Soviet Arts Festival, scheduled to begin Oct. 21. Noted mezzo-soprano Elena 
Obrazova of Moscow's Bolshoi Opera will sing the role of Marina, and Jansug 
Kakhidze will conduct Mussorgsky's epic opera. Kakhidze, the artistic director 
and chief conductor of the Tbilisi State Theatre, participated in Boston's 
American Soviet Festival in March, 1988. Nathaniel Merrill, general director of 
the Colorado Opera Festival, will be the production's stage director, and 
Soviet chorus master Natasha Promitko will assist local chorus master Martin 
Wright. Campbell will return to the Soviet Union in March to audition singers 
for the remaining "Boris Godunov" roles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
