<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: DANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN and Shauna Snow, Arts and entertainment reports from The 
Times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Film maker Steven Spielberg has donated $850,000 to the School of American 
Ballet in New York. The gift will be used to help build a special ballet studio 
now under construction at the school's new Lincoln Center facility, and will be 
the only one of five new studios to incorporate seating for student 
performances. The late George Balanchine and Lincoln Kirsten founded the school 
in 1934.ALEENE MacMINN and Shauna Snow 
</P>
</TEXT>
