<HEADLINE>
<P>
CATALANS TURN THUMBS DOWN ON BULLFIGHTS, POLL SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BARCELONA, Spain 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Catalans, always proud of the things that make them different from other 
Spaniards, disapprove of bullfighting, according to an opinion poll. 
</P>
<P>
The survey in the northeastern region published Tuesday showed 53% of Catalans 
questioned thought the sport should be banned, 12% thought it was cruel but 
should not be stopped and 23% thought it would be acceptable if it did not end 
with the death of the bull. 
</P>
<P>
Only 8% thought bullfighting was a good thing. 
</P>
<P>
The poll was carried out for the Catalan regional government, which last year 
became the first in Spain to introduce a law to protect animals against 
cruelty. 
</P>
<P>
The law does not prevent bullfights at permanent rings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021589-0078 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 18823 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 15, 1989, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
