<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOWN SEEKING LOST 1939 TIME CAPSULE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FAIRVIEW, Okla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City officials hope to open a time capsule, buried nearly 50 years ago, next 
October -- if they can find it. 
</P>
<P>
City Manager Jim Luckett Jr. said City Council minutes from 1939 refer to the 
capsule as commemorating the construction of City Hall. But the minutes do not 
say where the capsule was buried. 
</P>
<P>
Luckett said that either no marker was ever put on the capsule or it was 
covered during recent remodeling. 
</P>
