<P>
FULLERTON SCORES SCHOOL FIRST WITH TENNIS VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Fullerton women's tennis team defeated UC Irvine for the first 
time in school history, beating the Anteaters, 7-2, in a Big West Conference 
match Tuesday at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Nicole Brechtbuhl of Fullerton defeated Kathy Rose of Irvine at No. 1 singles, 
6-1, 6-3, and then combined with doubles' partner Colleen Duignan to defeat 
Rose and Cristi Bailey, 7-5, 7-6, at No. 1 doubles. 
</P>
<P>
Kelli Moore, Caroline Sporer, Lanna Hollo and Duiganan, also won in singles for 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Athletic Assn. men's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 5, UC Riverside 4 -- Olivier Amerlink and Allen Joinio of Chapman 
defeated Richard Beijer and Jim Wilbanks, 7-5, 7-5, at No. 1 doubles to decide 
the match at Chapman. Amerlink beat Nick Mateljan, 6-2, 6-2, Laurent Dropsy 
defeated Beijer, 0-6, 6-1, 6-2, and Joinio defeated Greg Skaggs, 7-5, 6-3, in 
singles. 
</P>
<P>
In doubles, Dropsy and Mick Zuercher defeated Skaggs and Kenin Klabunde, 6-4, 
7-5, also for Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 7, UC Irvine 4 -- Mike Grahovac had three hits, including a 
bases-loaded double in the first inning, for Chapman (4-6) at Irvine. Leading, 
5-4, in the ninth, Chapman scored two more runs. John Holshof got the victory 
and Jeff Haack took the loss. Ed Luna, a junior transfer from Rancho Santiago 
College, had three hits and three RBIs for Irvine (2-4-1). 
</P>
<P>
Southern California College 16, Redlands 4 -- Paul Plyler hit a grand slam in 
the first inning and Vance Castelow hit a solo shot for visiting SCC (3-1). Joe 
Aversa, a junior transfer from Golden West, pitched the first five innings for 
the victory. Aversa also had three hits. 
</P>
<P>
In Pac-10 wrestling: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton 19, Cal State Bakersfield 17 -- Fullerton rallied to win 
the final three matches at home. Ramon Diaz won at 177, Jose Flores won at 190 
but Fullerton still trailed, 17-16, going into the final match. Heavyweight 
David Jones then beat Tom Osendorf, 2-1, for Fullerton (13-6, 5-2). Bakersfield 
is 9-5-1, 3-1-1. 
</P>
