<P>
G. Lane Barnett has been appointed first vice president, director of product 
development and marketing, for Coldwell Banker Residential Group, Newport 
Beach. He will direct all national marketing activities, including advertising, 
public relations, research and product development for the company's more than 
2,100 residential real estate offices in the United States and Canada. Barnett 
succeeds Robert A. Rist, who has rejoined Sears, Roebuck &amp; Co.'s 
merchandise group as a national merchandise manager. Barnett was formerly 
senior vice president, director of marketing and advertising, for Jim Beam 
Brands Co. in Chicago. Before that, he held senior management positions with 
Royal Crown Cola Co., Mid-Continent Bottlers Inc. and Continental Can Co. 
