<P>
MURDOCH NEWS CORP. PROFITS UP 14% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rupert Murdoch's global media empire, News Corp. Ltd., today unveiled a 14.5% 
jump in operating earnings in the first half of its financial year, including a 
small profit for its fledgling Fox television network. 
</P>
<P>
News Corp. said its company-wide profit rose to $231 million in the six months 
ended Dec. 31 from $201 million a year earlier as sales jumped 21%. The results 
showed that the Fox Broadcasting Co., which News Corp. is trying to build into 
a fourth major U.S. television network, earned a small profit in the period, 
passing the break-even point in less time than most analysts had expected. News 
Corp. did not specify the amount of earnings produced by the unit, which had 
previously contributed a string of losses. Analysts figured it to be less than 
$1 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
