<P>
AGASSI ROUTS PUGH AT INDOOR EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MEMPHIS, Tenn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top-seeded Andre Agassi routed unseeded Jim Pugh 6-2, 6-3 as he opened defense 
of his title at the Volvo Indoor Tennis Championships. 
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Amos Mansdorf of Israel defeated Glenn Michibata of Canada, 
sixth-seeded Brad Gilbert defeated Scott Davis, 11th-seeded Michael Chang of 
Placentia beat Tom Nijssen of Holland, seventh-seeded Kevin Curren stopped 
Richard Matuszewski, 15th-seeded Derrick Rostagno lost in the second round to 
Pieter Aldrich of South Africa, Broderick Dyke of Australia defeated 
14th-seeded Paul Annacone, and No. 16 Johan Kriek defeated Bill Scanlon. 
</P>
<P>
And at the Virginia Slims tournament in Fairfax, Va., today, Steffi Graf 
dominated Carling Bassett-Seguso, yielding only 16 points in a 6-0, 6-0 victory 
that put her into the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
Graf, the world's top-ranked player, faced only three break points -- all in 
the same game -- in the 42-minute victory. With the exception of the fourth 
game of the second set, she surrendered only two points on her serve in her 
first-ever meeting with Canada's former No. 1 player. 
</P>
