<P>
STEVE LEWIS 'MALE ATHLETE OF YEAR' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UCLA's Steve Lewis, the gold medalist in the 400 meters in the 1988 Olympics, 
has been selected as Southern California's 1988 male athlete of the year by the 
Amateur Athletic Foundation of Los Angeles, it was announced today. 
</P>
<P>
The Southern California athlete of the year is selected by the AAF's Senior 
Awards Board, comprised of Southland sportswriters and sportscasters. Olympic 
sprinter Florence Griffith-Joyner was honored recently as female athlete of the 
year. Lewis, a 19-year-old UCLA sophomore, was chosen over a field that 
included UCLA quarterback Troy Aikman and USC quarterback Rodney Peete. Lewis 
captured the 400 meters in 43.87 seconds and also won a gold medal for being a 
part of the victorious U.S. 1,600-meter relay team. 
</P>
